cmnh1sk50004wk9083tm418ml	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.1a	Selection of participating MSMEs and cooperative enrollment.	The project team will identify, screen, and formally select the participating rural agro-food MSMEs and confirm the participation of the cooperative based on predefined eligibility and readiness criteria. The process will prioritize entities with clear interest in business improvement, digital adoption, value-added processing, and collaborative commercialization. Selected participants will be formally enrolled in the project through signed commitment forms and an agreed participation roadmap.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	0	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.917	2026-04-02 05:42:20.917
cmnh1sk53004yk908ydjky6ci	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.1b	Baseline assessment of business and financial management practices, digitalization, and export readiness.	The project team will conduct a structured baseline assessment of all selected participants to identify current capacities, constraints, and opportunities in business management, financial planning, basic costing, digital tool use, production recordkeeping, and export readiness. The assessment will generate an initial profile for each participant and establish baseline values for project monitoring, coaching, and tailored training.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	1	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.92	2026-04-02 05:42:20.92
cmnh1sk560050k908g291eguo	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.2	Design and delivery of tailored training program on international sustainable business models, export basics, and digital tools.	Co-design with participants and deliver a modular training program (presential and/or virtual) covering international sustainable business models, value proposition design, basic cost and price calculation, key steps and requirements for exporting to the United States, and use of digital tools.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	2	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.922	2026-04-02 05:42:20.922
cmnh1sk580052k908is89sbza	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.3	Individualized coaching for the cooperative and participating MSMEs on financial management, basic costing, and adoption of low-cost digital tools.	The project team will provide individualized coaching sessions tailored to the needs of the cooperative and each participating MSME. Coaching will focus on practical improvements in financial management, basic costing, pricing logic, cash-flow awareness, business decision-making, and the use of simple digital tools for recordkeeping and operational follow-up. The coaching process will translate training content into participant-specific action steps and reinforce adoption through direct follow-up and troubleshooting.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	3	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.925	2026-04-02 05:42:20.925
cmnh1sk5b0054k908ze1g7dqx	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.4	Development of individual business improvement and export-readiness plans incorporating digitalization strategies.	Facilitate the development of short, practical business improvement plans for each participating organization, including concrete actions, responsibilities, and timelines to strengthen their business model, digital capabilities, and prepare for future engagement with national and export markets.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	4	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.927	2026-04-02 05:42:20.927
cmnh1sk5f0056k908khponhfs	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.5	Detailed mapping of current business and production information flows.	Document existing processes for purchasing, inventory management, production, and, identifying critical control points, information gaps, and opportunities for simplification and digitalization.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	5	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.931	2026-04-02 05:42:20.931
cmnh1sk5h0058k9083i5agylz	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.6	Design, development, and configuration of low-cost digital tools and data structures.	Define and implement the minimum set of digital tools and standardized data fields required to register inventory movements, production batches, and sales in a way that supports future export requirements and can be maintained at near-zero cost.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	6	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.933	2026-04-02 05:42:20.933
cmnh1sk5j005ak9089ynfojgu	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.7	Training and on-the-job support for digital tool adoption.	Train staff from the cooperative and MSMEs on how to use the digital tools in their daily operations and provide on-the-job support during an initial implementation period to ensure correct data entry and routine use.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	7	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.936	2026-04-02 05:42:20.936
cmnh1sk5m005ck908iam2hd9r	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	cmnh1sk440048k9084ruajl94	activity	A1.8	Integration with weighing equipment and basic traceability records.	Set up data capture from industrial and portioning scales and link the resulting data to digital records of lots, products, and clients, creating a basic digital traceability chain from raw material intake to finished products.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	8	t	2026-04-02 05:42:20.938	2026-04-02 05:42:20.938
