cmnh1sk8k007qk908s0kfofna	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	\N	assumption	AS1	Assumptions	1. The MSMEs will be committed and actively participate in training, adoption of digital tools, and improvement processes.\n\n2. Access to internet and electricity in rural areas will be sufficient to implement and maintain the proposed digital and automation solutions.\n\n3. The equipment and technologies acquired will be compatible with local conditions and can be maintained with available resources and capacities.\n\n4. There will be no significant disruptions in the supply chain affecting the acquisition of inputs, equipment, or materials needed for the maquila and digitalization.\n\n5. Climatic and environmental conditions will allow continuous operation of production processes and the maquila, including the use of solar dehydrators.\n\n6. Local and national regulations will remain stable and favorable for the formalization, production, and export of MSME products.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	5	t	2026-04-02 05:42:21.045	2026-04-02 05:42:21.045
cmnh1sk8n007sk9089qqnjeuu	cmnh1sk3c003tk908gigp09oy	\N	external_factor	EF1	External Factors	1. Changes in international trade policies or tariffs that may affect exports to the United States or other markets.\n\n2. Variations in the national or global economic context impacting demand for agro-food products or MSMEs’ investment capacity.\n\n3. Extreme weather events or natural disasters that may affect agricultural production or maquila infrastructure.\n\n4. Changes in availability or cost of inputs, energy, or transportation that may affect project operations.\n\n5. Technological evolution that may require updating or adapting the implemented digital solutions.\n\n6. Changes in sanitary or quality regulations that may affect production or commercialization of products.\n\nSocial or community factors that may influence beneficiary participation and commitment.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	not_started	6	t	2026-04-02 05:42:21.048	2026-04-02 05:42:21.048
